script.name: Lib.Gen.Anarkis.ADS.Transfer.Crew
script.description: - Transfer ADS personell from one ADS asset to another - Swap duty of ADS personell on ADS assets

line.comment: * Usage: Create, transfer, buy or swap duty of ADS mechanics and marines from and to ships and stations
* Source and destination given and not identical, argument 'crew.member' is a mechanic or marine on source: Transfer this crew member from source to destination
* Source and destination given and not identical, number given, argument 'crew.member' is named as 'mechanics' or 'marines': Transfer number of crew members from source to destination
* Source and destination given and identical, argument 'crew.member' is a mechanic or marine on source: Swap duty of this crew member
* Source and destination given and identical, number given, argument 'crew.member' is named as 'mechanics' or 'marines': Swap duty of number of crew members
* No source given, destination given, number given, argument 'crew.member' defined as 'mechanics' or 'marines': Create number crew members in destination
* LU Update (Solarahawk): removed Player code
* Source is a ship
* Source is a station
* Destination is a ship
* Maximum allowed and current number of mechanics aboard ship
* Maximum allowed and current number of marines aboard ship
* Destination is a station
* Create array containing data about ADS mechanics and marines
* Maximum allowed and current number of mechanics aboard station
* Maximum allowed and current number of marines aboard station
* If source and destination are equal, swap duty
* Flag for later error report
* If no number given, loop runns only once, store original number
* Store original membership, if crew members are to swap duty, as membership will change during process
* Abort operation, if there is no more room for personell aboard ADS asset
* If an individual name was not given, pick first name in array
* Abort operation, if no crew member was to be found
* If a crew member is to swap duty, repeat loop with 'marines' as membership
* Abort operation, if there is no more room for personell aboard ADS asset
* If an individual name was not given, pick first name in array
* Abort operation, if no crew member was to be found
* If a crew member is to swap duty, repeat loop with 'mechanics' as membership
* Transfer / create crew
* do if $DEBUG == 1
* write to log file $page.id append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%sGoing to sub: Create.crew', $script.name, null, null, null, null
* do if $DEBUG == 1
* write to log file $page.id append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%sGoing to sub: Transfer.ship.to.ship', $script.name, null, null, null, null
* do if $DEBUG == 1
* write to log file $page.id append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%sGoing to sub: Transfer.ship.to.station', $script.name, null, null, null, null
* do if $DEBUG == 1
* write to log file $page.id append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%sGoing to sub: Transfer.station.to.ship', $script.name, null, null, null, null
* do if $DEBUG == 1
* write to log file $page.id append=[TRUE] printf: fmt='%sGoing to sub: Transfer.station.to.station', $script.name, null, null, null, null
* Sort crew arrays on destination stations
* Display error message, if something went wrong during transrer
* Marine swaps duty to mechanic
* Mechanic swaps duty to marine
* Transfer mechanic
* Transfer marine
* Transfer mechanic
* Delete passenger
* Transfer marine

* 0=name, 1=race, 2=voice, 3=face, 4=fighting skill, 5=hacking skill, 6=mechanical skill, 7=engineering skill, 8=status (ready, sleeping, training), 9=marine training course (all skills, fight, hack, eng, mech), 10=repair ratio, 11=price
* Delete marine
* Transfer mechanic
* Transfer marine
* Transfer mechanic
* Swap mechanic to marines
* Add mechanic to destination station
* Transfer marine
* Swap marine to mechanics
* Add marine to destination station

* 0=name, 1=race, 2=voice, 3=face, 4=fighting skill, 5=hacking skill, 6=mechanical skill, 7=engineering skill, 8=status (ready, sleeping, training), 9=marine training course (all skills, fight, hack, eng, mech), 10=repair ratio, 11=price

* 0=name, 1=race, 2=voice, 3=face, 4=fighting skill, 5=hacking skill, 6=mechanical skill, 7=engineering skill, 8=status (ready, sleeping, training), 9=marine training course (all skills, fight, hack, eng, mech), 10=repair ratio, 11=price
* Calculate and memory repair ratio
* Add member to asset
* Protection against too many crew members of the same name
* if find $ads.mechanic.name in array: $destination.mechanics.array
* do if !$source
* goto label Create.crew:
* end
* If player purchases personell form a station belonging to another race, charge money for member
* Try to drain money from destination first
